        "text_PJxJEe": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>You received The Tower because something in your life has already reached its breaking point, even if it still looks intact from the outside. This card comes to people who have been holding things together through willpower, adaptability, or responsibility rather than truth. You may be skilled at coping, smoothing over discomfort, or enduring situations longer than most would. Over time, this creates internal strain.<\/h3><h3>The Tower appears when your system knows that maintaining the current structure costs more than letting it fall. You may already sense this through restlessness, sudden clarity, or a growing intolerance for dynamics you once accepted. Chaos has likely been quietly building beneath the surface.<\/h3><h3>You received this card because you are ready to stop managing what was never sustainable, and instead, allow for old structures to be dismantled. Allow honesty, relief, and alignment to return to you. The Tower asks for your willingness to see clearly and to stop protecting any concept of false stability. <\/h3><h3>This card chooses people who are stronger than they realise, who are finally ready to choose the truth over the vast endurance they are capable of. What falls away now was not your foundation. <\/h3><h3>That foundation was always you. <br\/><br\/><strong>On Love<\/strong><\/h3><p>The Tower brings truth quickly. Relationships that survive this year will be grounded in pure honesty. Relationships that don’t survive the year will protect your future self. Stay true to yourself and your values, and allow clarity to replace confusion. <\/p><h3><strong>On Health<\/strong><\/h3><p>Stress demands release. If you experience sudden fatigue or tension, these are signs, and not failures. Rest and breathe. Caring for yourself must be non-negotiable. <\/p><h3><strong>On Money and Career<\/strong><\/h3><p>An unexpected change in work, role, or direction shakes things up but ultimately frees you. <\/p><h3><strong>How to work with this energy<\/strong><\/h3><p>Slow down and ground yourself. Let the dust settle before making big commitments. You will build with intention and even if it takes time, you will build well. <\/p><h3><strong>Recommended products<\/strong><\/h3><ol><li>Sunday Rituals Hair Repair & Growth Oil – Grounding, scalp massage for nervous system regulation<\/li><li>Squeeze the Day Bag Charm (Lemon) – Lightness after intensity<\/li><li>Enamel Pin (Ranunculus) – Freshness after change<\/li><\/ol><p>You can find these in our pop-up booth at Night At Orchard, along the outdoor pathway between Ngee Ann City & Ion Orchard between 26-28 Dec, 3pm onwards.<\/p>",
            "text_size": "typeset2",
            "secondary_color": false,
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
